We now illustrate how LDA can be combined with a neural network (see fig. 1). We feed a number of descriptors to the NN that reduces the dimensionality of the data through a succession of continuous non-linear transformations represented by fŒ∏(x) with parameters Œ∏. We then perform LDA on the topmost hidden space representation h = fŒ∏(x), and use the eigenvalues of eq. 4 to optimize the NN. From now on, we restrict the discussion to the typical case of two-classes, where the loss function reads:
L = ‚àív1 (5)
